text.tspan: Poles require special handling. Since cells are aligned to square boundaries, and cell midpoints correspond to vertices,
there is no single vertex that represents the pole. Leveraging the usual logic for vertex neighbors results in a gap near the pole.
Logic that would interpolate values for one would suffer a performance penalty,
so we are left to use the vertices that the grid already provides. Our solution is a special buffering class to handle polar faces.
Instances of this class use an id for an arbitrary square, i, to act as the axis of a triangle fan.
To prevent z-fighting between overlapping faces, only one instance of this class can be created per hemisphere.
